For Task 2, I set up my digital portfolio across two key professional platforms — GitHub and LinkedIn. These are among the most widely used platforms in the technology and engineering industry, and having a presence on them is an important first step toward building a professional identity as a student.
GitHub is a platform for hosting and sharing code repositories. It is widely used by developers, students, and companies worldwide. I created my profile README — a special repository that appears on my GitHub homepage — and filled it with my name, branch, year, and a short note about my learning goals. This acts as my digital introduction to anyone who visits my profile.
LinkedIn is a professional networking platform used by recruiters, companies, and working professionals. I set up my profile with my education details including my degree, institution, and expected graduation year.
I was surprised to see how many VIT alumni are already active on LinkedIn.
Over the next four years, I plan to use GitHub to showcase my projects and LinkedIn to connect with seniors, apply for internships, and follow industry trends.
